main event: A military observer reported sighting a white object in the sky resembling a star on February 3, 1964.
interesting points: The observation lasted for 5 minutes., The white object was seen on the horizon at 075 degrees true., The object was located about 030 degrees above the horizon., The sighting was during clear night skies., The observer had previously confirmed sightings of three satellites.
sighted object: a white object resembling a star
witness description: a military observer with past experience in satellite observations
